[thinking] I'm thinking about how Java compilation works. If a source file lacks a public class, javac will compile Other.class instead of Missing.class. This leads to the issue where using Files.readAllBytes(Missing.class) results in a NoSuchFileException, which, in turn, raises a DbException instead of simply returning null. It’s an interesting aspect of how file management and class compilation interact in Java!
