[thinking] I’m realizing there should be a one-to-one mapping between dynamic-access report classes and the generated test class files. I wonder if keeping the coverage for the active class in its own dedicated Java test file might complicate things by adding a helper file. Although a helper isn’t a test class, would it still be acceptable? To minimize issues, I could define a nested static helper in the test class, but the differing packages could pose a problem.
[thinking] 
[thinking] **Evaluating Java package rules**
[thinking] 
[thinking] I’m considering the mismatch between file path and package declaration in Java. It seems that when using javac with Gradle, the source file path doesn’t have to match the package — Gradle handles the scanning. So, I could have a file that’s not under the library package path, but the package declaration could still be `org.h2.util`. However, I should remember the rule against placing a test in the same package while keeping the declaration consistent.
[thinking] 
