fering packages could pose a problem.\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Evaluating Java package rules**\\n\\nI’m considering the mismatch between file path and package declaration in Java. It seems that when using javac with Gradle, the source file path doesn’t have to match the package — Gradle handles the scanning. So, I could have a file that’s not under the library package path, but the package declaration could still be `org.h2.util`. However, I should remember the rule against placing a test in the same package while keeping the declaration consistent.\"}]}"}, {"type": "toolCall", "id": "call_RLhIwJ1F0Tckjn7qjlWkmoW9|fc_05bb549048ace4550169f4ef7db0288195b7b5fc40974b6c77", "name": "write", "arguments": {"path": "tests/src/com.h2database/h2/2.1.210/src/test/java/org/h2/util/NullBytecodeSourceCompiler.java", "content": "/*\n * Copyright and related rights waived via CC0\n *\n * You should have received a copy of the CC0 legalcode along with this\n * work. If not, see <http://creativecommons.org/publicdomain/zero/1.0/>.\n */\npackage org.h2.util;\n\npublic class NullBytecodeSourceCompiler extends SourceCompiler {\n    @Override\n    byte[] javacCompile(String packageName, String className, String source) {\n        return null;\n    }\n}\n"}, "partialJson": "{\"path\":\"tests/src/com.h2database/h2/2.1.210/src/test/java/org/h2/util/NullBytecodeSourceCompiler.java\",\"content\":\"/*\\n * Copyright and related rights waived via CC0\\n *\\n * You should have received a copy of the CC0 legalcode along with this\\n * work. If not, see <http://creativecommons.org/publicdomain/zero/1.0/>.\\n */\\npackage org.h2.util;\\n\\npublic class NullBytecodeSourceCompiler extends SourceCompiler {\\n    @Override\\n    byte[] javacCompile(String packageName, String className, String source) {\\n        return null;\\n    }\\n}\\n\"}"}], "api": "openai-responses", "provider": "OCA", "model": "gpt-5.5", "usage": {"input": 2270, "output": 1194, "cacheRead": 30720, "cacheWrite":